Creates a new relationship object for the supplied parameters.

Parameters:
id - the relationship id. This is used as update key to the IPSConstants.PSX_RELATIONSHIPS table.
owner - the owner locator, not null.
dependent - the dependent locator, not null.
config - the relationship configuration, not null.

PSRelationship

protected PSRelationship(int id,
                         PSLocator owner,
                         PSLocator dependent)
Creates a new relationship object for the supplied parameters that allows derived classes to defer assignment of relationship configuration. Dervived classes must call setConfig(com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSRelationshipConfig) immediately after construction.

Parameters:
id - the relationship id. This is used as update key to the IPSConstants.PSX_RELATIONSHIPS table.
owner - the owner (parent) of the relationship, not null.
dependent - the dependent (child) of the relationship, not null.

setConfig

protected void setConfig(PSRelationshipConfig config)
Sets the configuration used for this relationship and initializes the user properties. This method only may be used after calling the constructor that allows deferred config assignment. This method may not be used to change an already assigned config.

Parameters:
config - the relationship configuration, not null.
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if this relationship has already been assigned a config.

resetId

public void resetId()
Method to reset the relationship id so that when saved will create a new relationship instead of modifying the existing one. This will be useful for example, when you have an existing relationship and want to create a new one based on this with some properties/attributes of the relationship changed.

fromXml

public void fromXml(Element sourceNode,
                    com.percussion.design.objectstore.IPSDocument parentDoc,
                    ArrayList parentComponents)
             throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
Description copied from interface: IPSComponent
This method is called to populate an object from its XML representation. An element node may contain a hierarchical structure, including child objects. The element node can also be a child of another element node.

Each component should add itself to parentComponents before constructing its child components, and should restore the original parentComponents before returning.

Parameters:
sourceNode - the XML element node to populate from, not null .
parentDoc - may be null.
parentComponents - a collection of all the components created in the process of creating this component. May be null.
Throws:
PSUnknownNodeTypeException - if the XML element node does not represent a type supported by the class.
See Also:
IPSComponent
